comment: If a class is a subclass of another class, then its power class is a subclass of that other class's power class. Left-to-right implication of Exercise 18 of [TakeutiZaring] p. 18. ~ sspwimpcf , using conventional notation, was translated from its virtual deduction form, ~ sspwimpcfVD , using a translation program.
